CHANGES0238 - Fix pre-existing nat arithmetic bugs in Part07 DecTC module

These bugs were masked by cached .agdai files and exposed when Part03
was modified (hiding φ from public export) in bck0237.

Files changed: Part07.agda (4141 → 4149, +8 lines)

Fixes:
1. TCmonoN k zero case: k ≠ k+0 definitionally. Added subst with
   sym (+-zero k) for base case and sym (+-suc k j) for suc case.
   Import: Cubical.Data.Nat.Properties (+-zero, +-suc, +-comm).

2. +-∸-< arithmetic lemma: <-+k gives a+(k∸b) < b+(k∸b), but
   ≤-∸-+-cancel needs (k∸b)+b. Added +-comm step.

3. splice/shortenChain: <-weaken (toℕ< j) gave toℕ j ≤ suc k,
   but needed toℕ j ≤ k. Fixed with pred-≤-pred (toℕ< j).

4. pigeonHole' call: FX FA were passed positionally but X,Y are
   implicit module params. Changed to {X = FX} {Y = FA}.

5. suc-≤-suc m<k: gave suc(suc m) ≤ suc k, needed suc m ≤ suc k.
   Fixed with suc-≤-suc (<-weaken m<k).

6. toℕ-injective antisym: arguments were in wrong order. Swapped.

7. transTC: chainToTC gives iterTC j', but subst expected
   iterTC ((m∸j')+j'). Restructured: chainToTC → TCmonoN → subst
   with +-comm ∙ ≤-∸-+-cancel.
